Here are some comments from a L15 Savage...<br>
<br>
<br>
&gt; Statistics<br>
Im not sure you emphasize this enough.<br>
Many devs seem to think that this is not so important because stats at high levels are effected so much by items. . .  but that does nothing but hurt the newbies/lowbies.<br>
<br>
&gt; I believe it is also necessary to make sure the Savage is:<br>
&gt; 1. On the heavy tank HP table, given that our special abilities cost health to use.<br>
&gt; 2. Using the heavy tank STR damage tables for their QUI/DEX weapons.<br>
I think you need to reinforce this, and add convincing arguements as to WHY.<br>
This is really important, but you dont justify it to the reader<br>
<br>
&gt; Savagery<br>
&gt; In many views, this should be the 'bread-n-butter' line <br>
However with the number of spec points we get, most people will be going H2H to 44-50 and that doesnt leave a whole helluva lot for savagery and parry....<br>
I think you should plug for more skill points here... (see below for more)<br>
<br>
&gt; Kelgor's Vigor Alteration<br>
EXCELLENT IDEA !!<br>
<br>
<br>
Hand-to-Hand<br>
&gt; The final concern is that our stun is secondary off a side-positional style.<br>
My personal view, it should be a REAR positional. Useful in RvR and PvE, <br>
but to change &quot;Clans Call&quot; to a side isn't a nice trade-off, SIDE positionals suck. Maybe FRONT?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&gt; Suggestions - Sense Aggression <br>
You could also add that this ability would be a good idea to help push Savagery to higher levels, but w/o more skill points, parry will suffer, still I think people would take it.<br>
<br>
<br>
SKILL POINTS?<br>
Savages like the berserker, we are a light tank that sacrifices defensive ability (armor and hps!) for offensive abilities.... Berserker gets massive damage output, we get speedy flurrys of smaller hits. BUT the Berserker gets 2.0 per level and we get 1.5.  <br>
To balance that 1.5 needs to be increased to 1.6 or 1.7.<br>
Its a tiny change that would ultimatly make all the difference in the world.<br>
For one, you wouldnt lose 1 spec point every other level!! <br>
(example, L7 7*1.5=10.5)  should be rounded up according to my grade school math teacher ;-) but DAOC rounds DOWN to 10, and we lose the spec point. I dont think that would happen with 1.6 or 1.7 per level.<br>
<br>
